Read `.pda/scripts/adapter.md`, section "Step 2".

Read `docs/pda-problem.md` and `docs/pda-solution-brief.md`. Prepare a structured specification prompt for `/speckit.specify` by extracting:

**From Problem Statement:**
- Element 1 (Gap) → why context
- Element 3 (Success criteria) → acceptance criteria
- Element 7 (Cost of inaction) → urgency

**From Solution Brief:**
- Section 2 (Proposed solution) → central "what"
- Section 3 (Key decisions) → prevent reinvention
- Section 4 (Business dimension) → components and structure
- Section 4 (Model dimension) → AI requirements (if applicable)
- Actor map → user context
- Section 6 (Success criteria) → acceptance per component
- Section 8 (Translatability map) → flag zones where agent must NOT invent

Present the assembled prompt to the human for review. Do NOT run /speckit.specify directly. Let the human execute it after reviewing and adjusting.
